{"id":"d=origam-topic-3958//p=0ba6b1ff676546c081af8189eb29a5e8","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3958"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["6ebbb511fca64ccbad83517a1a75e0cb"],"__file_part":["72b9df9ed83c44ef960096c9487244fb"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3958"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-edit-user-menu/3958"],"title":["How to edit user Menu"],"imagesFound":["5"],"imagesDescribed":["5"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d41a3639761e8685052355ec956582928f6f1215.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/356aab6956c219b7f4a75102d2dc286d2551e8a6.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3bd52dc1e661486ea8bacbb119daa78c5d190525.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/dac1067af83ae25d968c81e4fc6efba56e51ce5d.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/b5ebf41473574ffcb30584c7605d28ba443a627c.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to edit user Menu\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-edit-user-menu/3958\n\n@vikter (2025-02-17 12:04:42Z):\n   \n This guide will walk you through the process of editing the user menu in the client application. \n \n [!success]- Prerequisites for further work \n To proceed, ensure you meet the following five basic prerequisites: \n \n  Running a database server  \n  Running ORIGAM Server  \n  A project created in ORIGAM Architect  \n  A screen created  \n  The client application running in your browser  \n \n Once these prerequisites are set up, log into the client application using the  username and password you created  during the project setup. \n \n   Default Menu Items \n A fresh client application comes with a few items already present in the user menu: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d41a3639761e8685052355ec956582928f6f1215.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a UI sidebar for an application named \u0022Origam.\u0022 The sidebar includes a header with the title \u0022ORIGAM\u0022 at the top, followed by two sections labeled \u0022Work Queue\u0022 and \u0022Favourites.\u0022 Below these, there is a \u0022Menu\u0022 section containing various categories: \u0022Settings,\u0022 \u0022Maps,\u0022 and \u0022Users \u0026 Security.\u0022 Under \u0022Settings,\u0022 subcategories include \u0022General,\u0022 with further options like \u0022Features,\u0022 \u0022Languages,\u0022 \u0022Notification Templates,\u0022 \u0022Serial Number Ranges,\u0022 \u0022System Colors,\u0022 and \u0022Work Queues.\u0022 The \u0022Users \u0026 Security\u0022 category features options such as \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Add User,\u0022 \u0022Application Roles,\u0022 \u0022My User Profile,\u0022 \u0022User Permissions Overview,\u0022 \u0022User Roles,\u0022 and \u0022Users.\u0022 The apparent purpose of this interface is to provide navigation for configuration and management tasks within the Origam application.\n\n\n  \n This is the default state, and you are not permitted to make changes to it. However, if you wish to hide the entire  Settings  folder or its individual parts, you must do so via  role setup . \n   Creating custom Menu Items \n You can add custom items to the Menu manually or with Action and you can do it for screens, for sequential workflows and other model items. Here, we\u2019ll primarily show you how to work with screens, but the same approach applies to a sequential workflow as well. \n   Menu Item with Action \n If you use Action to create a Menu Item, you also create an Application Role to access it. \n To do so, run the Action  Create Menu Item  on the Screen (or Workflow) you want to add to your Menu: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/356aab6956c219b7f4a75102d2dc286d2551e8a6.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a software interface for application development, specifically focusing on the \u0022Screens\u0022 section. The UI shows a hierarchical file structure with entries for \u0022_system,\u0022 \u0022Dimensions,\u0022 and \u0022MyApplication.\u0022 A context menu is visible, displaying options such as \u0022New,\u0022 \u0022New Group,\u0022 \u0022Repeat New,\u0022 with a shortcut key of F12, and \u0022Actions.\u0022 Under \u0022Actions,\u0022 there are further options including \u0022Create Menu Item...\u0022 and \u0022Show XML.\u0022 The apparent purpose of this interface is to manage application screens and associated actions within a development environment.\n\n\n  \n Before using the new Application Role and Menu Item, remember executing the generated deployment script first. \n   Manual Procedure \n To add custom items to the menu manually, go to the Model Browser and navigate to  User Interface  /  Menu . Right-click on the Menu and select  New  /  Screen reference  (or  Sequential Workflow Reference ): \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3bd52dc1e661486ea8bacbb119daa78c5d190525.png]\nDescription: The image displays the Model Browser interface from a software application named \u0022myapplication.\u0022 It features a hierarchical tree structure on the left side, with sections labeled \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 and \u0022User Interface,\u0022 which includes subcategories such as \u0022Charts,\u0022 \u0022Dashboard Widgets,\u0022 \u0022Deep Link Categories,\u0022 \u0022Images,\u0022 \u0022Keyboard Shortcuts,\u0022 and another \u0022Menu.\u0022 Within the \u0022Menu\u0022 section, a context menu is open, showing options including \u0022New,\u0022 \u0022New Group,\u0022 \u0022Repeat New,\u0022 \u0022Actions,\u0022 \u0022Convert To,\u0022 \u0022Move To Package,\u0022 \u0022Edit item,\u0022 \u0022Delete,\u0022 and \u0022Execute.\u0022 The selected option in the menu is \u0022Screen Reference,\u0022 along with additional items like \u0022Data Constant Reference,\u0022 \u0022Sequential Workflow Reference,\u0022 \u0022Report Reference,\u0022 \u0022Dashboard,\u0022 and \u0022Dynamic Menu,\u0022 facilitating the user\u0027s navigation and management tasks within the application.\n\n\n","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:48:53"},"vector":[-0.008736046,-0.008146306,-0.06558519,-0.01835757,0.00027560876,-0.027506063,0.010417742,-0.007439884,0.008908006,0.0029784918,0.03032165,-0.018267544,-0.01743983,0.015912898,0.0033686173,-0.023728203,0.000514991,0.008062013,0.0014748205,0.0110962875,-0.00876427,0.01142264,0.024054067,0.027766842,-0.0051026815,0.03229482,-0.012972384,-0.043615066,-0.0032437707,-0.019422017,-0.007169647,-0.053174205,-0.033761997,-0.020760803,-0.004859125,0.015365451,-0.013284936,0.009212223,-0.043084454,0.014064851,-0.016822295,-0.012380019,-0.02943578,0.0118977185,-0.0008234578,-0.043417275,0.0076186988,0.0032622742,0.030367987,-0.06250605,-0.040708974,-0.010228764,0.016766462,-0.053604458,0.06333528,0.07558612,-0.023448497,-0.0030105864,-0.06685289,0.0243338,-0.0048850267,-0.0044473265,0.015806383,-0.03623615,0.015418693,-0.0065071993,0.0010029692,-0.010422592,-0.009512326,-0.041420072,-0.013556162,0.020518431,-0.040130343,-0.025881607,-0.067908294,0.0016136444,0.007889458,0.024244096,0.0039020148,0.047726072,-0.031904165,0.021657983,0.0129404515,0.0020267004,0.027272934,0.0120439865,-0.027946793,0.11302728,0.03490107,0.005179796,0.01011638,-0.029298179,0.049525913,-0.032006882,-0.02242867,0.012118858,-0.02415445,-0.0031166477,0.00080536574,0.014973734,-0.05267075,-0.017625935,0.005449621,-0.0017245067,-0.0040577045,0.025971448,0.020620126,-0.004235029,0.022525745,-0.048055697,-0.011482734,0.009004217,0.0312579,-0.017449217,0.011325896,-0.03565089,0.028358798,-0.062356133,-0.0006099606,0.012280507,-0.024643965,0.023864508,0.055969305,-0.020770494,0.00034828292,0.05000363,0.02406798,-0.007938881,-0.01167045,-0.00414